2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a new information dimension based on the Tsallis entropy, which is a concept from information theory. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the structure of complex networks and how different parts of the network influence the information dimension. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The concept of self-similarity and fractals, which are discussed in the paper, are also relevant in the field of neural and evolutionary computing. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The study of complex networks has applications in various fields, including computational engineering, finance, and science.
